The error `TS18047: 'redis' is possibly 'null'` happens because TypeScript's strict null checks cannot guarantee that the imported `redis` object is still available inside the asynchronous `stream.on('data', ...)` callback, even if you checked it at the top of the function.

To fix this, I will update `server/src/lib/cache.ts` to assign `redis` to a local constant (e.g., `client`) after the check. TypeScript can then confidently infer that this local constant is never null inside the callback.

